definition.value: Anxiety is a neurological and physiological symptom characterized by a painful or apprehensive uneasiness of mind usually over an impending or anticipated ill.

Urticaria is a skin and integumentary tissue symptom characterized 
by raised red skin wheals (welts) commonly caused by an allergic reaction with wheals that may vary in size from about 5 mm (0.2 inches) in diameter to the size of a dinner plate that are described as severely itchy a stingnig or burning sensation, and having a pale border.

Heartburn is a pain characterized by a painful burning feeling in your chest or throat that happens when stomach acid backs up into your esophagus.
Nausea is a digestive system symptom characterized by an uneasy or unsettled feeling in the stomach together with an urge to vomit.
A symptom is a perceived change in function, sensation, loss, disturbance or appearance reported by a patient indicative of a disease.
Headache is a pain characterized by a pain in the head.
Insomnia is a sleep disturbance characterized by prolonged and usually abnormal inability to obtain adequate sleep.
Dizziness is a neurological and physiological symptom characterized by a sensation of unsteadiness accompanied by a feeling of movement within the head.

Stroke is a nervous system symptom characterized by a sudden diminution or loss of consciousness, sensation, and voluntary motion caused by rupture or obstruction (as by a clot) of a blood vessel of the brain.
Constipation is a feces and droppings symptom involving the abnormally delayed or infrequent passage of dry hardened feces.

A nervous system symptom that involves, is related to, or emphasizes behavior.
Function-related process is a process that related to the execution of a function, a metafunction, and the malfunction.
This tree is based on a functional concept ontology (Kitamura 2002).

Primitive process is a unit of process.
Process series at a certain granular level can appear as one primitive process at the higher level.

Whether the process is a primitive process or not depends on the setting of the granularity.
When one does not consider the details more than a certain level, or a level as the minimum grain size, the process at that level becomes the primitive process.

A role played by the entity which enables the facilitated diffusion of an ion (by an energy-independent process) by passage through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel without evidence for a carrier-mediated mechanism. May be either selective (it enables passage of a specific ion only) or non-selective (it enables passage of two or more ions of same charge but different size).

Functioning process is a subtype of function-related process: A process that executes and manifests function.
Malfunctioning process is a subtype of function-related process: A process that cannot perform a function appropriately or cannot realize it at all.
Dysfunctioning is a subtype of malfunctioning process: A process that performs an abnormal and incomplete functioning.
Starvation is a subtype of depleting: A process that lessens markedly in quantity of the nourishment.
Catalysis role of the phosphorylation of an amino acid residue in a protein, usually according to the reaction: a protein + ATP = a phosphoprotein + ADP.
Mitochondrial dysfunction is a subtype of dysfunctioning: A process that performs an abnormal and incomplete mitochondrial function.
Protein aggregation is a subtype of molecular assembly: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of molecules.
Catalysis role of the reaction: N-acylsphingosine + H2O = a fatty acid + sphingosine.
A role which enables the directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

A role played by the entity to initiate or regulate transcription.
This term is sometimes used for both gene regulatory proteins as well as the general transcription factors.
